This paper deals with communication systems and coding strategies, which are typically studied in the Information Theory (cs.IT) and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Wyner-Ziv compression, which falls under the Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of structured lattice codes, which are commonly studied in the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper addresses power allocation and coefficient selection, which are relevant to the Computer Engineering (cs.CE) sub-category.
